# Badge — Styles

CSS file: `@acko/css/badge.css`

## Architecture

ALL styling in CSS via `@apply` + raw CSS. React only composes class names via `clsx`.

## CSS Classes

### Base
`.acko-badge` — `inline-flex items-center font-medium whitespace-nowrap rounded-full leading-none` with `gap: var(--scale-4)`

### Text Case
No lowercase words in badges. Three case variants:

| Class | CSS | Default |
|-------|-----|---------|
| `.acko-badge-uppercase` | `text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em` | Yes (default) |
| `.acko-badge-title-case` | `text-transform: capitalize` | — |
| `.acko-badge-sentence-case` | `text-transform: none` | — |

### Sizes
| Class | Padding | Font | Width |
|-------|---------|------|-------|
| `.acko-badge-sm` | `4px 8px` | `--font-label-sm-size` | `fit-content` |
| `.acko-badge-md` | `6px 8px` | `--font-caption-size` | `fit-content` |
| `.acko-badge-lg` | `8px` | `--font-body-sm-size` | `fit-content` |

### Solid Variant Colors
Pattern: `.acko-badge-solid-{color}` where color = `purple | green | blue | orange | pink | gray`

Uses gradient fill + border:
- `background: linear-gradient(0deg, --color-badge-{color}-gradient-from, --color-badge-{color}-gradient-to)`
- `border: 1px solid --color-badge-{color}-border`
- `color: --color-badge-{color}-text`

Green badge uses lime primitives for gradient/border, green for text.

### Outline Variant Colors
Pattern: `.acko-badge-outline-{color}`

Uses token: `--color-badge-{color}-outline-color` for both text and border. Green outline uses `lime-600`.

### Dot Variant Colors
Pattern: `.acko-badge-dot-{color}`

Same gradient + border as solid + `.acko-badge-dot` child element (`--scale-6` circle in `currentColor`)

### Children
- `.acko-badge-dot` — `--scale-6` circle indicator
- `.acko-badge-remove` — remove button with X icon (`--scale-12` SVG)

### Counter Badge
- `.acko-counter-badge` — pill with min-width `--scale-20`, height `--scale-20`, padding `0 --scale-6`, font `--font-label-sm-size`, tabular-nums, text `--color-on-primary`
- `.acko-counter-badge-{color}` — purple, pink, blue — gradient fill + border:
  - `background: linear-gradient(0deg, --color-counter-{color}-gradient-from, --color-counter-{color}-gradient-to)`
  - `border: 1px solid --color-counter-{color}-border`
